    <text>
        <body>
        	<div1 type="letter">
        		<pb entity="DSSR_000001107_0379"/>
        		<head>Jim to Mademoiselle Marcelle Guerin, Sunday <date value="1916-07-16"> July 16th 1916</date></head>
        		
        		<opener>
            <dateline>Sunday <date value="1916-07-16">July 16th 1916</date></dateline>
            
            <salute>Dear Marcelle:</salute>
        		</opener>
        		
            <p>
            I was very
            pleased to get your
            letter this morning and
            to learn that the
            rest cure is coming on
            so well.
            </p><p>
            I’m sorry to
            tell you that I can’t
            get the photos of
            machines in the clouds
            I promised you.  I wrote
            to the man and he tells
            
            <pb entity="DSSR_000001107_0381" n="[p.2]"/>
            
            me he can’t let me have
            them.
            </p><p>
            The dog hasn’t
            shown up as yet.
            Your suggestion about
            my taking my permission
            at Evian les Bains sounds
            fine &mdash; but its too late 
            now.  I’ve just been
            thinking it over this
            morning, and how delightful
            it would be to walk
            around the charming country
            with you &mdash; we’d have
            
            <pb entity="DSSR_000001107_0380" n="[p.3]"/>
            
            the dog along, of course,
            to chase the golf  balls
            you lost and then we’d
            sit down where we 
            could get a glimpse of
            the deep blue lake and
            I could make love to
            you and drink Evian
            sparkling H2O.  No, but 
            seriously, it would be 
            fine &mdash; a real rest 
            and the best of company.
            However its moonlight
            
            <pb entity="DSSR_000001107_0382" n="[p.4]"/>
            
            now and I’m afraid I
            might get foolish, and
            then afterwards feel as 
            badly as I did for long 
            after that night we
            docked at Havre which 
            seems a few hundred
            years ago.
            </p>
        		
        		<closer>
            <salute>More anon<lb/>
            
            My best</salute>
            
            <signed>Jim</signed>
            
            <seg type="postscript">
            My best wishes and
            regards to your mother.
            <lb/><lb/>
            I enclose photo
            of Victor I told
            you of.
            </seg>
        		</closer>
            
            <!-- [With this letter is an envelope addressed to Mademoiselle Marcelle Guerin, Hotel l’ Ermitage, Evian les Bains, Haute - Savoie.] -->
            
